# Development overview

Explain how contributors change the project safely and consistently.

Cover the project-specific development concerns that matter, such as:

- repository layout and important module boundaries;
- local setup and supported toolchain;
- build, test, lint, and validation commands;
- extension points and implementation conventions;
- migration or compatibility practices;
- common failure modes and lessons learned.

Add focused pages as these concerns become concrete. The [Feature Lifecycle](feature-lifecycle.md) defines how planned work moves through design, review, implementation, documentation, validation, and delivery.
